  }\\n\\n    static class SocketFactory extends PlainConnectionSocketFactory {\\n        private final ClickHouseConfig config;\\n\\n        private SocketFactory(ClickHouseConfig config) {\\n            this.config = config;\\n        }\\n\\n        @Override\\n        public Socket createSocket(final HttpContext context) throws IOException {\\n            return AbstractSocketClient.setSocketOptions(config, new Socket());\\n        }\\n\\n        public static SocketFactory create(ClickHouseConfig config) {\\n            return new SocketFactory(config);\\n        }\\n    }\\n\\n    static class SSLSocketFactory extends SSLConnectionSocketFactory {\\n        private final ClickHouseConfig config;\\n\\n        private SSLSocketFactory(ClickHouseConfig config) throws SSLException {\\n            super(ClickHouseSslContextProvider.getProvider().getSslContext(SSLContext.class, config)\\n                    .orElse(SSLContexts.createDefault()),\\n\\n[106 more lines in file. Use offset=401 to continue.]\"}], \"isError\": false, \"timestamp\": 1778182851095}}\n3933:[recv] {\"type\": \"turn_end\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"thinking\", \"thinking\": \"**Exploring output stream features**\\n\\nIt seems that the output stream feature could be something new. If I'm considering the request.output(OutputStream), then the sealedRequest.getOutputStream would likely be passed to a post. I wonder if implementations simply copy the response to the output while leaving the response input empty? It might be worth inspecting further to see how this actually works in practice and what implications it might have. There’s a lot here to think about!\", \"thinkingSignature\": \"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"rs_0d5854a86fc9171e0169fceac06cf08197ab6fe4e749807a41\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"reasoning\\\",\\\"encrypted_content\\\":\\\"gAAAAABp_OrCOVe-M9EpfGXKfHwU72wU2Urm26YJA4Cj5xV1yDRxQnmGKJkafGC1rBnF7OlzWEoHr69GmSovfLEL9svy-FJGQi5y6zG91lqsQXSGB46cwA9yWKl592hsBPoxN4SXtNQjspy