SKILL.md:3:description: Review automated pull requests with the `library-bulk-update` label in graalvm-reachability-metadata. Use when asked to review or triage a PR that bumps tested versions for existing libraries, including approve vs close decisions, CI checks, diff-scope validation, and verification of `source-code-url`, `test-code-url`, `documentation-url`, and `repository-url` changes.\\n./skills/review-library-bulk-update/SKILL.md:8:These PRs are created by the scheduled compatibility workflow and are expected to update supported library versions by changing `metadata/**/index.json`.\\n./skills/review-library-bulk-update/SKILL.md:24:   - Read the body and verify it is a bot-generated \\\"Added tested versions\\\" summary.\\n./skills/review-library-bulk-update/SKILL.md:29:   - Normal change shape: new values appended to `tested-versions`, with formatting-only line movement around the surrounding JSON.\\n./skills/review-library-bulk-update/SKILL.md:35:     - matching `index.json` changes to `metadata-version`, `tested-versions`, and exact-version artifact URLs\\n./skills/review-library-bulk-update/SKILL.md:47:   - Added tested versions should match the actual JSON changes.\\n./skills/review-library-bulk-update/SKILL.md:57:   - Confirm the new versions were added under the correct `metadata-version` entry.\\n./skills/review-library-bulk-update/SKILL.md:58:   - Preserve existing ordering conventions; new tested versions are typically appended in version order.\\n./skills/review-library-bulk-update/SKILL.md:59:   - Do not accept dropped tested versions, entry reshuffling, or unrelated field edits without a clear reason.\\n./skills/review-library-bulk-update/SKILL.md:60:   - For pre-release promotions, confirm `metadata-version` moved from the matching pre-release to the corresponding full release, old pre-release values were removed from `tested-versions`, and any `test-version` references were updated only when they pointed at the promoted test directory.\\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:17:- Be more relaxed than `library-new-request`: do not reject only because a test resembles older coverage, stays in an existing package layout, or contains compatibility branches for multiple supported versions.\\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:40:   - Accept compatibility edits that keep one test source working across multiple tested versions.\\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:51:   - Compatibility branches are acceptable when they keep older and newer tested versions covered by the same test.\\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:56:4. Check dynamic-access coverage across versions.\\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:87:- Dynamic-access coverage does not drop between the previous and new tested versions, or any apparent drop is convincingly explained by a changed upstream API/runtime surface.\\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:110:- For coverage drops: say that dynamic-access coverage must not regress between tested versions, cite the old and new values, and ask for either restored coverage or a concrete explanation.\\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:116:- For version-pinned tests: say that tests should not reference the exact library version because the same test should support multiple library versions.\\n./skills/review-library-new-request/SKILL.md:20:- Do not accept tests that reference the exact library version in test code or assertions unless the version check is itself the behavior under test. One test should remain valid across multiple supported library versions.\\n./skills/review-library-new-request/SKILL.md:80:  - The test logic is version-agnostic and can cover multiple supported versions of the same library.\\n./skills/review-library-new-request/SKILL.md:99:- For version-pinned tests: say that tests should not reference the exact library version because the same test should support multiple library versions.\\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:42:   - Accept narrow test edits that keep the same behavior covered across old and new versions.\\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:53:4. Check dynamic-access coverage across versions.\\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:84:- Dynamic-access coverage does not drop between the previous and new tested versions, or any apparent drop is convincingly explained by a changed upstream API surface.\\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:107:- For coverage drops: say that dynamic-access coverage must not regress between tested versions, cite the old and new values, and ask for either restored coverage or a concrete explanation.\\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:17:- Be more relaxed than `library-new-request`: do not reject only because a test resembles older coverage, stays in an existing package layout, or contains compatibility branches for multiple supported versions.\\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:40:   - Accept compatibility edits that keep one test source working across multiple tested versions.\\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:50:   - Compatibility branches are acceptable when they keep older and newer tested versions covered by the same test.\\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:54:4. Check dynamic-access coverage across versions.\\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:84:- Dynamic-access coverage does not drop between the previous and new tested versions, or any apparent drop is convincingly explained by a changed upstream API surface.\\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:107:- For coverage drops: say that dynamic-access coverage must not regress between tested versions, cite the old and new values, and ask for either restored coverage or a concrete explanation.\\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:112:- For version-pinned tests: say that tests should not reference the exact library version because the same test should support m